39:41.838 --> 39:45.001
— The True wasn't mine.
- But still...

39:51.848 --> 39:53.839
I'm happy for him.

39:55.143 --> 39:57.555
(Both laughing)

39:57.688 --> 40:00.896
I am. I'm... I'm happy.

40:02.943 --> 40:04.934
(On radio: J‘ Hip—hop)

40:11.952 --> 40:13.943
(Music stops)

40:22.421 --> 40:24.412
Ready to open?

40:26.466 --> 40:28.206
Miss LaDee?

40:31.305 --> 40:32.920
I gotta go.

40:33.056 --> 40:34.842
Sorry.

40:46.403 --> 40:48.689
(Hidalgo) You'll like this offer.
(Man) Not interested.

40:48.822 --> 40:51.188
You and your wife are gonna be very happy
with this offer.

40:51.325 --> 40:54.158
— We're paying top dollar.
— Not interested.

40:54.286 --> 40:56.402
— Hear me out, sir.
— I'm not selling.

40:56.538 --> 40:59.701
Not ever.
Not after what I've been through.

40:59.833 --> 41:03.417
When I leave here, it'll be feet first.

41:06.214 --> 41:10.457
(Albert) I wanna talk to you about our drummer.
(Delmond) You don't think Carl Allen's subtle?

41:10.594 --> 41:12.425
— Really?
— Too damn subtle.

41:12.554 --> 41:16.046
I hired him and Ron Carter
'cause I figured you'd like 'em —

41:16.183 --> 41:18.674
two classic jazz men
right up your alley.

41:18.810 --> 41:20.311
Not for what I'm trying to do.

41:20.437 --> 41:24.350
I need somebody like
Earl Palmer or Herman Ernest.

41:24.483 --> 41:26.314
For what you trying to do?

41:26.443 --> 41:28.434
Shit, for my part, yeah.

41:28.570 --> 41:32.062
We could get somebody
like Uganda Roberts

41:32.199 --> 41:35.111
to come up here and work
as your percussion man.

41:35.243 --> 41:38.986
Carl ain't gonna mind another percussionist
working with us. We could bring somebody up.

41:39.122 --> 41:41.408
No, no, we gotta take this whole thing
down to New Orleans.

41:41.541 --> 41:44.829
— The entire session?
- It don't feel right.

41:44.961 --> 41:47.452
— I can't do it here.
—(Laughs)

41:49.675 --> 41:52.257
— What?
— Listen to you, Daddy.

41:52.386 --> 41:54.468
Can't nobody play the drums, play a bass line,

41:54.596 --> 41:56.382
cook a steak or fry a fish up here.

41:56.515 --> 41:59.757
In all of New York, New York,
can't nobody do nothing to suit you.

41:59.893 --> 42:01.679
Look, I know what's right and what ain't.

42:01.812 --> 42:05.054
- No, you know what you know.
— Yeah, well, if I don't know it by now,

42:05.190 --> 42:06.305
fuckit

42:06.441 --> 42:08.853
Always the last damn word.
Always the last fucking word.

42:08.985 --> 42:12.068
Always need it, always want it,
always gonna have to have it, huh, Daddy?

42:13.240 --> 42:15.105
(Truck horn blasts)

42:15.242 --> 42:16.778
Nope.

42:16.910 --> 42:18.571
(Car honks)

42:18.704 --> 42:21.616
— (Foghorn)
— (King) Your brother named one of the officers.

42:21.748 --> 42:25.081
We have that name. We're just asking you
to confirm that it's the right name.

42:25.210 --> 42:26.791
George told you a name, it's on him.

42:26.920 --> 42:29.252
I don't want police knowing we spoke.

42:29.381 --> 42:32.088
— You have our word.
— Police not gonna do shit anyhow.

42:32.217 --> 42:33.627
They won't, people don't step up.

42:33.760 --> 42:36.968
— Can't argue with that.
— Please, Miss Beaulieu.

42:37.097 --> 42:40.635
I can't help you all.
I gotta live here, you know.

42:45.188 --> 42:48.351
- (Don) Huh.
— (Cornell grunts)

42:50.569 --> 42:53.606
— Damn, dog, you really driving.
— (Don laughs)

