43:52.130 --> 43:53.745
Lady lawyer, eh?

43:53.882 --> 43:55.998
I see you brought
the cavalry with you today.

43:56.134 --> 43:58.045
You plainclothes or Homicide?

43:58.178 --> 44:00.294
- Neither.
— Oh, a bodyguard.

44:00.430 --> 44:03.263
— Yeah, you smart to bring protection, lady.
- I'm Toni Bernette.

44:03.391 --> 44:06.599
I don't work for or with the police.
You remember.

44:06.728 --> 44:10.596
(Exhales sharply) I remember. And I remember
telling you I don't remember anything else

44:10.732 --> 44:13.724
— about what happened at that damn store.
— Billy Wilson.

44:13.860 --> 44:17.102
That's the name of the cop
that showed up at Robideaux's.

44:17.239 --> 44:20.026
He's one of them
who did the dirt there, right?

44:20.742 --> 44:23.575
We got the name from someone
who saw Officer Wilson

44:23.703 --> 44:26.115
chase a man into a unit at the Iberville,

44:26.248 --> 44:27.909
likely the same afternoon.

44:28.041 --> 44:30.248
Also shot dead, same caliber weapon.

44:31.419 --> 44:34.206
We've got two people dead behind this
and no one wants to talk.

44:34.339 --> 44:36.421
Yeah, well, people dying
all the time round here.

44:36.550 --> 44:39.792
— That's just how it go.
— If you intimidated, I can understand that.

44:41.638 --> 44:44.004
That's what they count on —
folks staying frightened.

44:44.140 --> 44:45.880
— Motherfucker, I ain't afraid.
- I'm just saying.

44:46.017 --> 44:48.724
- I ain't fucking afraid of no one.
— Nobody's afraid, but no one says a word.

44:48.854 --> 44:50.685
You think I wasn't willing to give my name?

44:50.814 --> 44:55.103
You think I'm just gonna let someone
shoot people down and not say something?

44:55.235 --> 44:57.521
Yeah, that's right.

44:57.654 --> 44:59.485
I already fucking gave my name.

44:59.614 --> 45:03.527
— What?
— I called the police. I gave my name.

45:03.660 --> 45:06.367
— Who did you talk to?
— Man, I called 911.

45:06.496 --> 45:09.909
I told her I saw the police shoot a boy down
for no damn reason.

45:10.041 --> 45:12.874
I gave 'em my name.
I gave 'em my cell phone number too.

45:13.003 --> 45:14.743
And what happened next?

45:14.880 --> 45:18.043
About two weeks later,
this detective calls me,

45:18.174 --> 45:20.256
arranges to come past
by my mother's house.

45:20.385 --> 45:23.422
He said, "If you wanna come forward
and tell 'em what you saw, it's no problem.

45:23.555 --> 45:26.092
"We'll take you right downtown,
let you make a statement.

45:26.224 --> 45:28.089
"When they pump the water
out of the courthouse,

45:28.226 --> 45:30.638
— "we'll take you over there, say the same."
— And did you?

45:30.770 --> 45:34.012
No, 'cause the next thing
this cop tells me

45:34.149 --> 45:36.310
is that before
I can make my statement

45:36.443 --> 45:39.276
he needs my name,
my date of birth,

45:39.404 --> 45:41.941
my mother's name,
her date of birth.

45:42.073 --> 45:44.155
Do the same
for everybody living in her house,

45:44.284 --> 45:47.026
for all your kinfolk
and for everybody who we hang with.

45:47.162 --> 45:51.201
He said if he find any paper
on any one of my people

45:51.333 --> 45:54.575
or anybody who got anything to do with me,
they all going to jail.

45:54.711 --> 45:56.326
He threatened you that way?

45:56.463 --> 46:00.456
So now you see why I managed
not to remember a damn thing.

46:01.384 --> 46:05.377
But yeah, Wilson was there.
He always been an asshole.

46:05.513 --> 46:09.347
And another one I remember, too, from
around the way — white cop named Harvin.

46:11.019 --> 46:12.884
I gave him that name too.

46:13.021 --> 46:15.979
— Sorry for doubting you there, bro.
— Yeah, I bet.

46:16.107 --> 46:19.099
The detective — his name?
You remember?

46:20.111 --> 46:21.487
French, I think.

46:21.613 --> 46:23.569
Prioleau?

46:24.366 --> 46:25.822
Prioleau.

46:32.165 --> 46:33.905
I'll come back on the weekend.

46:34.042 --> 46:35.623
You know, I replaced that one.

46:35.752 --> 46:37.663
The roof? Nice job.

46:37.796 --> 46:40.959
Damn straight. It should last 10, 15 years.

46:51.059 --> 46:54.893
If Homicide came out on this, then there
should be a record of the 911 call in the file.

46:55.021 --> 46:56.602
Yeah, there should be.

46:56.731 --> 46:59.268
There should also be
a first officer's report,

46:59.401 --> 47:03.440
and bullet casings that were recovered
and God knows what else.

47:03.571 --> 47:06.608
Either it's stuck in a drawer or in some file
somewhere in Homicide.

47:06.741 --> 47:08.481
Yeah, or just gone,

47:08.618 --> 47:11.781
disappeared like everything else.

47:13.373 --> 47:16.706
But you're right — it all goes back
to the homicide unit.

47:16.835 --> 47:19.952
— That's where the dirt is on this.
- You know anyone up there?

47:22.549 --> 47:23.959
(Knocks on door)

47:26.344 --> 47:28.255
— You wanted to see me?
- (Oliver) come in.

47:28.388 --> 47:30.003
Close the door for me.

47:34.019 --> 47:35.634
Sit down.

47:41.401 --> 47:45.235
Yesterday I let you talk and I didn't say
too much about what you told me,

47:45.363 --> 47:48.196
so now I'm gonna talk.

47:49.659 --> 47:52.526
OK, then, your people didn't raise you
to get in a car with kids

47:52.662 --> 47:54.698
you knew were the no—account kind.

47:54.831 --> 47:57.322
But, young lady,
your mother has it hard right now.

47:57.459 --> 48:00.075
Your dad's gone
and what she's got left is you.

48:00.211 --> 48:03.544
